[normal]BCS
[normal] is governed by a Royal Charter which defines our purpose: to promote the study and practice of Computing and to advance knowledge and education for the benefit of the public. We bring together over 70,000 industry, academics, practitioners and government 
[normal]to share knowledge, promote new thinking, inform the design of new curricula, shape public policy and inform the public.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]As a professional body, 
[normal]BCS
[normal] represents its members and the IT Profession as a whole on issues of importance, and liaises with other pr
[normal]ofessional bodies, the government, industry and academics to initiate and inform debate on IT strategic issues. We also deliver a range of professional development tools for practitioners
